- --------------------------------------------------------------------------
CONECTIVA LINUX SECURITY ANNOUNCEMENT 
- --------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGE   : kdenetwork
SUMMARY   : Fix for kppp vulnerability
DATE      : 2005-03-16 14:31:00
ID        : CLA-2005:934
RELEVANT
RELEASES  : 9

- -------------------------------------------------------------------------

DESCRIPTION
 kppp[1] is the KDE[2] internet dialer.
 
 This announcement fixes a privileged file descriptors leak
 vulnerability[3,4] which could allow local attackers to hijack a
 system's domain name resolution function.


SOLUTION
 It is recommended that all kppp users upgrade their packages.
 
 
 REFERENCES
 1.http://freshmeat.net/projects/kppp/
 2.http://www.kde.org
 3.http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CAN-2005-0205
 4.http://www.kde.org/info/security/advisory-20050228-1.txt


